comments: the shapes that shared colours had the same ending - which perhaps indicates the masculine, feminine, gender neutral and plural versions of the words like in other languages like french. It was easy to generally understand what shape it was that we were looking for based on the start of the word like wopi = circular shape. I wish I had gotten more time to practise it to get better at memorising the endings for each colour. I think the most difficult part to get a grasp of was the spellings versus the pronunciations because some of them sounded the same but were spelled differently and it got confusing
